The paper deals with the computation of tree-width and path-width, which are fundamental concepts in graph theory and are widely used in computer science. The paper presents a more efficient algorithm to compute the path-width and provide a path decomposition. This suggests that the paper is likely to be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
